# Integration Hub CSS Fixes - Cursor Rules

## Quick Fix for Input Margin Issues

When working on integration hub components, follow these patterns:

### Input Element Guidelines

```typescript
// ❌ AVOID: Direct margin on input elements
<input className="mb-6 w-full border rounded" />

// ✅ PREFER: Wrap inputs in containers for spacing
<div className="mb-6">
  <input className="w-full border rounded" />
</div>
```

### CSS Override Rules

```css
/* Apply this CSS to fix existing integration hub issues */
.integration-hub input {
  margin-bottom: 0 !important;
}

.integration-hub .form-field {
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}
```

### Component Pattern

```tsx
// Recommended pattern for integration hub forms
const IntegrationHubInput = ({ label, ...props }) => (
  <div className="mb-6"> {/* Spacing on container */}
    <label className="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">
      {label}
    </label>
    <input 
      className="w-full px-3 py-2 border rounded-md" // No margin classes
      {...props} 
    />
  </div>
);
```

### Quick Fix Commands

1. Find all `mb-6` classes on input elements
2. Move margin classes to parent containers
3. Apply CSS override if needed immediately

